@startuml deployment_flow
!define AWSPUML https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awslabs/aws-icons-for-plantuml/v14.0/dist
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff

title Deployment Workflow - From Image to Kubernetes

actor User
participant "CLI/API" as Interface
participant "Orchestrator" as Orch
participant "LLM" as LLM
participant "State Manager" as State
participant "K8s Manifests" as K8sMani
participant "Argo CD" as ArgoCDSys
participant "Kubernetes" as K8s

User -> Interface: deploy --image automotive-trace32:latest
Interface -> Orch: deploy_image(image_id, replicas, env)

Orch -> State: create_deployment(pending)
State --> Orch: deployment_id

Orch -> LLM: generate_deployment_manifest(\n  image_id, replicas, env, namespace\n)
LLM --> Orch: manifest_dict\n(deployment, service,\nresources, health_checks)

Orch -> State: update_deployment(manifest_ready)

Orch -> K8sMani: apply_manifest(manifest)
K8sMani -> K8sMani: render_yaml
K8sMani -> K8s: kubectl apply -f manifest.yaml
K8s --> K8sMani: resources_created

Orch -> State: update_deployment(deploying)

Orch -> ArgoCDSys: sync_application(\n  app_name,\n  manifest\n)

ArgoCDSys -> ArgoCDSys: create/update\nApplication CRD
ArgoCDSys -> K8s: auto-sync deployment
K8s -> K8s: pull_image_from_registry
K8s -> K8s: create_pods
K8s -> K8s: health_checks

Orch -> State: update_deployment(deployed)

ArgoCDSys --> Orch: sync_status

note right of ArgoCDSys
  Argo CD watches repository
  and automatically syncs
  any configuration changes
end note

note right of K8s
  Kubernetes manages:
  - Pod lifecycle
  - Rolling updates
  - Health checks
  - Resource limits
  - Auto-scaling (if HPA)
end note

Orch --> Interface: {\n  "success": true,\n  "deployment_id": "...",\n  "status": "deployed"\n}

Interface --> User: ✓ Deployment successful!

User -> K8s: kubectl get pods -n automotive-tools
K8s --> User: POD_NAME   READY  STATUS\ntrace32-xxx   1/1    Running\ntrace32-yyy   1/1    Running

@enduml
